title.narrative: By 2020, strengthened sub-national level human and institutional capacities to coordinate, monitor and evaluate Government multi-sectoral, food and nutrition security policies and action plans

description.narrative: Progress continued on strengthened capacities for coordination, monitoring, and evaluation of multisectoral nutrition action plans, particularly at subnational level in Nampula, Zambezia, and Sofala provinces. Nampula and Zambezia, in their fourth year of programme implementation, hosted a successful exchange visit for the Sofala GT-PAMRDC, who were in their first year of implementation. All 13 districts supported by UNICEF developed action plans for stunting reduction. UNICEF Nutrition and Social Policy teams worked to ensure that “Food and Nutrition Security” is defined in Mozambique’s new budget structure, which will enable financial tracking and advocacy for longer term nutrition investments across sectors. | Status:Met | As-of Date:02/02/2022
